    "body": "PR Breakdown\r\n============\r\n\r\nIssue\r\n-------\r\nThere are currently is 14 different \"array\" data types in the types version. Every time a minecraft updates adds a new \"type\" of/ array, we are forced to create a three new functions, one new type, etc...\r\nThis has led to the packet definition being unclear (What is a mapChunkBulk ? What is a statistic array ?) and the source of protocol.js to be ridiculously big.\r\n\r\nProposed Fix\r\n------------------\r\nWe should replace the different data types with a simple and flexible system. \r\n\r\nEvery types can have access to \"typeArgs\", which can define some options that are only given for that data type. \r\n\r\nThe following four data types : \r\n- container, pretty much defines a javascript object. Takes a \"fields\" array in it's typeArgs.\r\n- count, a hack that uses an array/buffer as its value instead of the given one. Takes a \"type\" and a \"countFor\" string in its typeArgs\r\n- array, represents a length-prefixed array. Takes a \"type\" and a \"count\" string in its typeArgs.\r\n- buffer, a specialized array for \"bytes\" that return a nodejs Buffer, instead of a js array. Takes a \"count\" string in its typeArgs\r\n\r\nAll of those can be nested, which allows for nearly every complex data types to be broken down into simpler ones. \r\n\r\nExamples : \r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n   map_chunk_bulk:     {id: 0x26, fields: [\r\n        { name: \"chunkColumnCount\", type: \"count\", typeArgs: { type: \"short\", countFor: \"meta\" } },\r\n        { name: \"dataLength\", type: \"count\", typeArgs: { type: \"int\", countFor: \"compressedChunkData\" } },\r\n        { name: \"skyLightSent\", type: \"bool\" },\r\n        { name: \"compressedChunkData\", type: \"buffer\", typeArgs: { count: \"dataLength\" } },\r\n        { name: \"meta\", type: \"array\", typeArgs: { count: \"chunkColumnCount\", \r\n          type: \"container\", typeArgs: { fields: [\r\n            { name: \"x\", type: \"int\" },\r\n            { name: \"z\", type: \"int\" },\r\n            { name: \"bitMap\", type: \"ushort\" },\r\n            { name: \"addBitMap\", type: \"ushort\" }\r\n        ] } } }\r\n      ]},\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote : needs to be extensively tested with an actual server. All tests currently pass, but I didn't really test on minecraft server.",
